data_summary_share_Green_Electricity <- kaggle_data %>%
  group_by(Year) %>%
  summarise(
    share_of_renewable = 100 * (sum(`Electricity_renewables`, na.rm = TRUE) / 
    (sum(`Electricity_fossil`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_nuclear`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_renewables`, na.rm = TRUE))),
    share_of_nuclear = 100 * (sum(`Electricity_nuclear`, na.rm = TRUE) / 
    (sum(`Electricity_fossil`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_nuclear`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_renewables`, na.rm = TRUE))),
    share_of_fossil = 100 * (sum(`Electricity_fossil`, na.rm = TRUE) / 
    (sum(`Electricity_fossil`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_nuclear`, na.rm = TRUE) + 
     sum(`Electricity_renewables`, na.rm = TRUE))))
  
ggplot(data_summary_share_Green_Electricity, aes(x = Year)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = share_of_renewable, color = "Renewable")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = share_of_nuclear, color = "Nuclear")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = share_of_fossil, color = "Fossil Fuels")) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("Renewable" = "blue", "Nuclear" = "green", "Fossil Fuels" = "red"),
    name = "Energy Source"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Year",
    y = "Share of Total Electricity Generation (%)",
    title = "Electricity Generation Shares by Energy Source Over Time"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")

# Ensure numeric data types for calculations
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(
    CO2_emissions_per_capita = as.numeric(CO2_emissions_per_capita),
    Population = as.numeric(Population)
  )

# Calculate total CO2 emissions by multiplying per capita emissions by population
co2_time <- merged_data %>%
  filter(Year != 2020) %>%  # Exclude 2020
  mutate(Total_CO2 = CO2_emissions_per_capita * Population / 1e6) %>%  # Convert to million metric tons
  group_by(Year) %>%
  summarise(Total_CO2 = sum(Total_CO2, na.rm = TRUE))

# Generate the line plot

  geom_line(color = "blue", size = 1) +
  labs(title = "Global Total CO2 Emissions Over Time",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Total CO2 Emissions (Million Metric Tons)") +
  theme_minimal()

## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (3): Entity, Time Code, Country Code
## dbl (21): Year, Population, Access_to_electricity, Access_to_clean_fuels, Re...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Ensure correct column names and convert to numeric
merged_data <- merged_data %>% 
  mutate(
    Financial_flows = as.numeric(Financial_flows),
    Population = as.numeric(Population),
    Renewable_energy_share = as.numeric(Renewable_energy_share),
    Year = as.numeric(Year)
  )

# Identify the top 10 countries with the largest total financial flows
top_countries <- merged_data %>% 
  group_by(Entity) %>% 
  summarise(Total_Financial_Flows = sum(Financial_flows, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(Total_Financial_Flows)) %>% 
  head(10) %>% 
  pull(Entity)

# Filter the dataset for only the top 10 countries and calculate total financial flows per country
top_financial_data <- merged_data %>% 
  filter(Entity %in% top_countries) %>% 
  group_by(Entity) %>% 
  summarise(Total_Financial_Flows = sum(Financial_flows, na.rm = TRUE))

# Create the bar graph
ggplot(top_financial_data, aes(x = reorder(Entity, Total_Financial_Flows), y = Total_Financial_Flows)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "skyblue") + 
  coord_flip() +  # Flip coordinates for better readability of country names
  labs(
    title = "Total Financial Flows for Clean Energy Projects",
    subtitle = "Top 10 Countries by Cumulative Financial Flows (USD)",
    x = "Country",
    y = "Total Financial Flows (USD)"
  ) + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 12)
  ) +

# Load the merged dataset
merged_data <- read_csv("merged_population_economic_data.csv")
## Rows: 3417 Columns: 24
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (3): Entity, Time Code, Country Code
## dbl (21): Year, Population, Access_to_electricity, Access_to_clean_fuels, Re...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Rename columns for consistency (if needed)
colnames(merged_data)[colnames(merged_data) == "Financial flows to developing countries (US $)"] <- "Financial_flows"
colnames(merged_data)[colnames(merged_data) == "Renewable energy share in the total final energy consumption (%)"] <- "Renewable_energy_share"

# Convert necessary columns to numeric
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(
    Financial_flows = as.numeric(Financial_flows),
    Population = as.numeric(Population),
    Renewable_energy_share = as.numeric(Renewable_energy_share)
  )

# Calculate Financial Flows per Capita
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(Financial_flows_per_capita = Financial_flows / Population)

# Calculate Percentage Change in Renewable Energy Share (Year-over-Year)
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  arrange(Entity, Year) %>%  # Ensure correct ordering
  group_by(Entity) %>%
  mutate(Renewable_change = (Renewable_energy_share - lag(Renewable_energy_share)) / lag(Renewable_energy_share) * 100) %>%
  ungroup()

# Remove rows with missing values
clean_data <- merged_data %>%
  filter(!is.na(Financial_flows_per_capita), !is.na(Renewable_change))

# Create Scatter Plot with Trend Line
ggplot(clean_data, aes(x = Financial_flows_per_capita, y = Renewable_change)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5, color = "blue") +  # Scatter plot points
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", se = TRUE) +  # Trend line with confidence interval
  labs(title = "Financial Flows per Capita vs. Change in Renewable Energy Share",
       x = "Financial Flows per Capita (USD)",
       y = "Percentage Change in Renewable Energy Share (%)") +
  theme_minimal()

# Load necessary libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(readr)

# Load the merged dataset
merged_data <- read_csv("merged_population_economic_data.csv")
## Rows: 3417 Columns: 24
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (3): Entity, Time Code, Country Code
## dbl (21): Year, Population, Access_to_electricity, Access_to_clean_fuels, Re...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Ensure correct column names
colnames(merged_data)[colnames(merged_data) == "gdp_per_capita"] <- "GDP_per_capita"
colnames(merged_data)[colnames(merged_data) == "Renewable energy share in the total final energy consumption (%)"] <- "Renewable_energy_share"
colnames(merged_data)[colnames(merged_data) == "Primary energy consumption per capita (kWh/person)"] <- "Primary_energy_per_capita"

# Convert necessary columns to numeric
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(
    GDP_per_capita = as.numeric(GDP_per_capita),
    Renewable_energy_share = as.numeric(Renewable_energy_share),
    Primary_energy_per_capita = as.numeric(Primary_energy_per_capita),
    Population = as.numeric(Population)
  )

# **Drop 2020 data if needed**
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  filter(Year < 2020)

# **Categorize Countries into GDP Groups (Low, Middle, High Income)**
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(Income_Group = case_when(
    GDP_per_capita < 5000 ~ "Low Income",
    GDP_per_capita >= 5000 & GDP_per_capita < 20000 ~ "Middle Income",
    GDP_per_capita >= 20000 ~ "High Income"
  ))

# **Summarize Data by Income Group & Year**
summary_data <- merged_data %>%
  group_by(Year, Income_Group) %>%
  summarise(
    Avg_GDP_per_capita = mean(GDP_per_capita, na.rm = TRUE),
    Avg_Renewable_share = mean(Renewable_energy_share, na.rm = TRUE),
    Total_Population = sum(Population, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Remove N/A Income Groups
summary_data <- summary_data %>% filter(!is.na(Income_Group))

# Improved Scatter Plot: GDP vs. Renewable Energy
ggplot(summary_data, aes(x = Avg_GDP_per_capita, y = Avg_Renewable_share, size = Total_Population, color = Income_Group)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +  # Trend line
